@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    .privacy-card {
        background: #242526;
        border: 1px solid #3a3b3c;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 36px 40px;
        max-width: 780px;
        margin: 30px auto;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
        animation: fadeUp .35s ease both;
    }
    @@keyframes fadeUp {
        from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
        to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
    .privacy-card h1 {
        color: #e4e6eb;
        font-size: 26px;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
    }
    .privacy-card h1 i { color: #2d88ff; }
    .privacy-updated {
        color: #b0b3b8;
        font-size: 13px;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
    }
    .privacy-card h2 {
        color: #e4e6eb;
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin: 28px 0 12px;
        padding-bottom: 8px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #3a3b3c;
    }
    .privacy-card p, .privacy-card li {
        color: #b0b3b8;
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .privacy-card ul {
        padding-left: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .privacy-card li {
        margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .privacy-card a {
        color: #2d88ff;
        text-decoration: none;
    }
    .privacy-card a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }
</style>

<div class="privacy-card">
    <h1><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> @ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <div class="privacy-updated">Last updated: March 28, 2026</div>

    <p>
        At <strong>Zuvo</strong>, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
        use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our social media platform.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Username, email address, password (hashed), profile picture, bio, location, date of birth, and gender.</li>
        <li><strong>Content:</strong> Posts, comments, reactions, and images you publish on the platform.</li>
        <li><strong>Social Data:</strong> Friendships, friend requests, and group memberships.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Login timestamps, pages visited, and interactions with content.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>To create and manage your account.</li>
        <li>To display your posts, comments, and reactions.</li>
        <li>To facilitate social connections (friend requests, suggestions).</li>
        <li>To provide real-time notifications and messaging.</li>
        <li>To improve and personalize your experience on the platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell, trade, or rent your personal data to third parties.
        Your content is shared only with other users of the platform as intended by the platform's features
        (e.g. posts are visible to other logged-in users, profile information is visible on your profile page).
    </p>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Password hashing using industry-standard algorithms (ASP.NET Core Identity).</li>
        <li>CSRF protection on all form submissions.</li>
        <li>HTTPS encryption for data in transit.</li>
        <li>Authorization checks to ensure users can only modify their own data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        We use cookies to maintain your login session. These are essential cookies required for the platform to function.
        Session cookies expire when you close your browser; persistent cookies (if "Remember Me" is selected) expire after 7 days.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access and update your profile information at any time.</li>
        <li>Change your password.</li>
        <li>Remove your profile picture or cover photo.</li>
        <li>Delete your posts and comments.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact the platform administrator.
    </p>
</div>
